{"sha": "8a96884981c97c4c35e304004290271308a67637", "node_id": "C_kwDOAAsO6NoAKDhhOTY4ODQ5ODFjOTdjNGMzNWUzMDQwMDQyOTAyNzEzMDhhNjc2Mzc", "commit": {"author": {"name": "Nilstrieb", "email": "48135649+Nilstrieb@users.noreply.github.com", "date": "2022-09-27T18:56:05Z"}, "committer": {"name": "Nilstrieb", "email": "48135649+Nilstrieb@users.noreply.github.com", "date": "2022-09-27T18:56:05Z"}, "message": "Flush delayed bugs before codegen\n\nSometimes it can happen that invalid code like a TyKind::Error makes\nits way through the compiler without triggering any errors (this is\nalways a bug in rustc but bugs do happen sometimes :)). These ICEs\nwill manifest in the backend like as cg_llvm not being able to get\nthe layout of `[type error]`, which makes it hard to debug. By flushing\nbefore codegen, we display all the delayed bugs, making it easier to\ntrace it to the root of the problem.", "tree": {"sha": "d65ed037add268a9ce4204ae8f1ae5a10f1db4f4", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/trees/d65ed037add268a9ce4204ae8f1ae5a10f1db4f4"}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/commits/8a96884981c97c4c35e304004290271308a67637", "comment_count": 0, "verification": {"verified": true, "reason": "valid", "signature": "-----BEGIN SSH SIGNATURE-----\nU1NIU0lHAAAAAQAAADMAAAALc3NoLWVkMjU1MTkAAAAgbSfWKRQb2tiqhuHtakDJeupmrF\nChDbM0msU+PXaBOk8AAAADZ2l0AAAAAAAAAAZzaGE1MTIAAABTAAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5\nAAAAQKPbPr5oaA/YjnNW2HaQyU06pyxOb4asG+Wgq0Nl5h8pFHwZI3YTpo4u1vvB7dRNAW\neDzl2LlXd56bS9jmr3AAM=\n-----END SSH SIGNATURE-----", "payload": "tree d65ed037add268a9ce4204ae8f1ae5a10f1db4f4\nparent 57ee5cf5a93923dae9c98bffb11545fc3a31368d\nauthor Nilstrieb <48135649+Nilstrieb@users.noreply.github.com> 1664304965 +0200\ncommitter Nilstrieb <48135649+Nilstrieb@users.noreply.github.com> 1664304965 +0200\n\nFlush delayed bugs before codegen\n\nSometimes it can happen that invalid code like a TyKind::Error makes\nits way through the compiler without triggering any errors (this is\nalways a bug in rustc but bugs do happen sometimes :)). These ICEs\nwill manifest in the backend like as cg_llvm not being able to get\nthe layout of `[type error]`, which makes it hard to debug. By flushing\nbefore codegen, we display all the delayed bugs, making it easier to\ntrace it to the root of the problem.\n"}}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/8a96884981c97c4c35e304004290271308a67637", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/commit/8a96884981c97c4c35e304004290271308a67637", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/8a96884981c97c4c35e304004290271308a67637/comments", "author": {"login": "Nilstrieb", "id": 48135649, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjQ4MTM1NjQ5", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/48135649?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Nilstrieb", "html_url": "https://github.com/Nilstrieb", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Nilstrieb/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Nilstrieb/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Nilstrieb/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Nilstrieb/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Nilstrieb/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Nilstrieb/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Nilstrieb/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Nilstrieb/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Nilstrieb/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "committer": {"login": "Nilstrieb", "id": 48135649, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjQ4MTM1NjQ5", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/48135649?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Nilstrieb", "html_url": "https://github.com/Nilstrieb", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Nilstrieb/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/u